data.title: Wonderful tour of historical site!
data.text: Spend a leisurely walk through downtown Lancaster, PA. A slow paced tour through over 280 years of Lancaster rich history.

data.title: Walk, look, listen, learn
data.text: This is organized by the City Tourism Office (I think). You sign up (small fee) at the tourist information space across from the Central Market. We enjoyed it-- especially going into Trinity Church (even if you DON'T go on the tour DO GO into this church and take a good look, especially at the tiles and stained glass and graveyard). The tour could have been in greater depth. Too much --here's where each native son lived, worked etc-- and far too little depth on the social/cultural/political development of the area.
